## Takeaway

The key idea is to first count the frequency of every element using a **HashMap**. Then, maintain a **Min Heap of size `k`** that stores only the `k` most frequent elements. Whenever the heap grows larger than `k`, remove the element with the smallest frequency. This ensures an efficient **O(n log k)** solution without sorting all elements.
